	Sometimes /etc/resolv.conf gets garbage to the 'search' line.
	Looks like dhclient has trouble with the 'prepend' configuration
	and string data.

How-To-Repeat: 
	/etc/dhclient.conf:

		interface ep0 {
			prepend domain-name "z ";
			prepend domain-name-servers 127.0.0.1;
			script "nonexistent_just_testing_dhclient"
		}

	# dhclient -d -D ep0

	Now files /tmp/dcs* might contain trash in new_domain_name variable.
	Varying the length of the z above can reveal or hide the bug.
